<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-19T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-19T20:00:00-05:00" n="187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2131/45: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-19T20:00:00-05:00">August 19, 1933—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>74. Legation’s 73, August 14, 5 p.m. Francisco Restrepo Plata and Arturo
                            Hernandez, members of the Supreme Customs Tribunal, are being appointed
                            advisers in lieu of Guzmán and will leave shortly. Publicity not yet
                            given here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>